summary: If Arya goes to serve under a courtesan i’ll be curious to see which one it is. I’ve narrowed my guess down to three.  1. The...
body:
If Arya goes to serve under a courtesan i’ll be curious to see which one it is. I’ve narrowed my guess down to three. 

1. The Black Pearl
I’ve talked about her before and how i think she will be important to Arya’s story, but on top of the fact that i think she will be the one to teach Arya about politics (that’s going on the assumption that is based off of the famed courtesan Veronica Franco), she also plays into Arya’s connection with the Targaryens. 

Bellegere Otherys is the great grand-daughter of Bellegere Otherys (for whom she is named), who was a lover of Aegon IV Targaryen. Considering the fact that Arya has an interesting amount of dragon imagery for a Stark and strongly resembles a woman who had a role (most likely a rather unwilling one) in the events that would lead to the Targaryens being exiled. Also if R+L=J is true a Targaryen just died for her in the form of Jon being murdered in ADWD, then Arya has a pretty solid connections to the Targaryen family. By training with Bellegere she would be strengthening that connection.

The Black Pearl is also pretty likely because the Kindly Man already offered to send Arya to her. 

“Or would you sooner be a courtesan, and have songs sung of your beauty? Speak the word, and we will send you to the Black Pearl or the Daughter of the Dusk. You will sleep on rose petals and wear silken skirts that rustle when you walk, and great lords will beggar themselves for your maiden’s blood.” - Arya II, AFFC

Also the Black Pearl comes up in several of Arya’s chapters in Braavos. We see her/hear about her with Cat and Mercy. I dont think George would bring her up so often if she was unimportant.  

2. The Moonshadow

Okay this one is unlikely, but it would be rather satisfying if only because i love Arya’s moon imagery. We only hear about her once and it is only in passing. 

“…the Moonshadow wore only white and silver…” - Cat of the Canals, AFFC

Again this has more to do with Arya’s association with the moon and shadows than the relationship between the two, so it is pretty unlikely. 

3. The Merling Queen

Less likely than the Black Pearl, but more likely than the Moonshadow, the Merling Queen is the only one who Arya notices almost as much as she notices the Black Pearl. While we dont know much about her we do know she actually takes on apprentices. 

“the Merling Queen was never seen without her Mermaids, four young maidens in the blush of their first flowering who held her train and did her hair.” - Cat, AFFC

“The Merling Queen has chosen a new Mermaid to take the place of the one that drowned. She is the daughter of a Prestayn serving maid, thirteen and penniless, but lovely.“ - Cat, AFFC

There is a bit to unpack with that last sentence, especially how the Kindly Man reacts to it. Depending on how you read it, it can come off as pretty dark. The point is that we know in TWoW Arya is supposed to get her moon blood and she is supposed to turn twelve. Arya would fit the requirements and her relationship with water would work in this situation, though it would work with the Black Pearl too. 

If Arya does get sent to a courtesan my money is on the Black Pearl, she just comes up way too much for her to be meaningless. At the same time until TWoW comes out i can still amuse myself by taking guesses.

summary: I Get a Little Warm in My Heart When I Think of Winter
title: I Get a Little Warm in My Heart When I Think of Winter
body:
Author: Chash

Fandom: Game of Thrones

Rating: Mature (for sex)

Words: 8,123

Summary: Arya Stark returns to Winterfell to discover they have a new bastard smith, and he has a new daughter who likes to play with swords.

Link: https://archiveofourown.org/works/2479127

Review: I felt this was very true to what could have happened in Game of Thrones if Gendry had a child. I loved the relationship shown between Arya and Gendry, the banter and how their relationship alters a bit years after they last saw each other (the Brotherhood in this fic).

summary: She puts his body in the sky, turns his being into stars and tells people it is to honor her friend. That’s true, it is, but...
caption:
She puts his body in the sky, turns his being into stars and tells people it is to honor her friend. That’s true, it is, but it’s not her only reason. She does it to ease her own guilt at her dear companion’s death. She does it because she’s a little less lonely when she looks to the sky and see him staring down on her. 

Arya x Gendry as Artemis and Orion
